Definition.WordDefinition: Sargo \Sar"go\, n. [Sp. sargo, L. sargus a kind of fish.] (Zo["o]l.) Any one of several species of sparoid fishes belonging to {Sargus}, {Pomadasys}, and related genera; -- called also {sar}, and {saragu}. [1913 Webster]
